 mine."},{"id":"marker96","name":"Roresvi — silver mining town","legend":"Roresvi is a mining town of 23879 people just nearby the silver mine."},{"id":"marker97","name":"Cambucalia — iron mining town","legend":"Cambucalia is a mining town of 8367 people just nearby the iron mine."},{"id":"marker98","name":"Monch — iron mining town","legend":"Monch is a mining town of 8258 people just nearby the iron mine."},{"id":"marker99","name":"Bongenbach Bridge","legend":"A wooden bridge spans over the Bridge River near Bongenbach."},{"id":"marker100","name":"The Pink Crow","legend":"A big and famous roadside tavern. Delicious mashed spinach with green liquor is served here."},{"id":"marker101","name":"The Major Crane","legend":"A big and famous roadside tavern. Delicious jugged cabbage with white gin is served here."},{"id":"marker102","name":"The Fair Inn","legend":"A big and famous roadside inn. Delicious syrupped pepper with misty whisky is served here."},{"id":"marker103","name":"Southttirean Lighthouse","legend":"A lighthouse to serve as a beacon for ships in the open sea."},{"id":"marker104","name":"Kinbunddum Lighthouse","legend":"A lighthouse to serve as a beacon for ships in the open sea."},{"id":"marker105","name":"Kharakhelese Waterfall","legend":"The cascades of a stunning waterfall."},{"id":"marker106","name":"Boyran Waterfall","legend":"The rapids of an exceptionally beautiful waterfall."},{"id":"marker107","name":"Bridgewich Waterfall","legend":"A breathtaking waterfall cuts through the landscape."},{"id":"marker108","name":"Epepelian Waterfall","legend":"A breathtaking waterfall cuts through the landscape."},{"id":"marker109","name":"Shulukkhaz Waterfall","legend":"A gorgeous waterfall flows here."},{"id":"marker110","name":"Zadzah Waterfall","legend":"A river drops down from a great height forming a wonderous waterfall."},{"id":"marker111","name":"Nin'jassi Battlefield","legend":"A historical battle of the Pusaqat Conquest. \r\nDate: April 6, 1380 Crering Era